# ── SuperBrowser deploy (runagent) — environment ──────────────────────────────
# Used two ways, both reading the SAME secrets:
#   • `runagent deploy` merges + uploads this .env; the serverless engine writes
#     it to /root/.env inside the VM.
#   • `docker compose up` loads it (env_file) into the all-in-one local container.
# Infra defaults (HEADLESS, PORT, Chromium path, cookie-jar/profile persistence,
# HTTP/2 off) are baked into the image — you only set secrets and optional
# features here. Copy this file to `.env` and fill it in.
#
# You do NOT put a RunAgent (rau_) key here. The local container never needs one;
# the rau_ key is only for the host SDK when remote=True (which bypasses Docker).

# ── REQUIRED: the agent brain ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Two ways to pick the brain. Use the SAME one your host `npm run dev` uses so
# Docker behaves identically (a different/weaker model is the single biggest
# cause of "works on the host, misbehaves in Docker").
#
# (A) EXACT parity — deliver your whole ~/.nanobot/config.json verbatim. This
#     reproduces the model AND the loop tuning (maxToolIterations, maxTokens,
#     contextWindowTokens, reasoningEffort, temperature, …) plus the provider
#     key. RECOMMENDED when you drive the host in-process and want a match.
#       NANOBOT_CONFIG_JSON_B64=$(base64 -w0 ~/.nanobot/config.json)
#     ⚠️  When you use (A), keep LLM_MODEL UNSET below. deploy/main.py passes
#         model=$LLM_MODEL into SuperBrowser(model=...), which OVERRIDES the B64
#         config's model — setting both silently reverts you to LLM_MODEL.
#
# (B) Model-only — set a model + exactly ONE provider key. Simpler, but you get
#     nanobot's built-in default loop tuning, not the host's.
#       LLM_MODEL=gpt-4o
#       OPENAI_API_KEY=            # ...or LLM_PROVIDER/LLM_MODEL/LLM_API_KEY, or ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
#
# Keep a provider key present regardless: the TS engine uses OPENAI_API_KEY for
# its built-in captcha/vision, and _has_llm_credentials() needs a key to run.
# LLM_MODEL=gpt-4o
OPENAI_API_KEY=
# ...or use Anthropic instead of OpenAI:
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# NANOBOT_CONFIG_JSON_B64=

# ── OPTIONAL: cheap vision model for screenshots (recommended for browser mode) ─
# VISION_ENABLED=1
# VISION_PROVIDER=gemini
# VISION_MODEL=gemini-2.0-flash-exp
# VISION_API_KEY=

# ── OPTIONAL: captcha auto-solve ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# CAPTCHA_PROVIDER=2captcha
# CAPTCHA_API_KEY=

# ── OPTIONAL: proxies (datacenter / residential) ──────────────────────────────
# PROXY_POOL=http://user:pass@host:port
# PROXY_POOL_RESIDENTIAL=http://user:pass@host:port

# ── OPTIONAL: URL firewall + human-handoff webhook ────────────────────────────
# FIREWALL_ALLOW_LIST=example.com,github.com
# FIREWALL_DENY_LIST=evil.example.com
# HANDOFF_WEBHOOK_URL=https://your-bot.example.com/webhooks/handoff
